83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
Senate Concurrent Resolution 207
Sponsored by Senator WAGNER (Presession filed.)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: Fixes firm dates for measures during session. (Flesch Readability Score: 66.7).
Establishes deadlines and procedural rules for completion of legislative measures for the 2026
regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly.
1 CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 Be It Resolved by the Legislative Assembly of the State of Oregon:
3 (1) This resolution constitutes a rule of proceeding of the Senate and the House of Represen-
4 tatives of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly.
5 (2) The Senate and the House of Representatives shall adhere to the following schedule and
6 deadlines for the 2026 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly:
7 (a) The Senate and the House of Representatives shall convene in regular session on February
8 2, 2026.
9 (b) Committee chairpersons shall schedule work sessions for measures in the chamber of origin
10 no later than February 9, 2026. This paragraph does not apply to:
11 (A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
12 (B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, Joint Committee
13 on Transportation Funding and Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
14 (C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
15 Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
16 mittee on Conduct.
17 (c) Committees shall consider measures in the chamber of origin no later than February 16, 2026.
18 This paragraph does not apply to:
19 (A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
20 (B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, Joint Committee
21 on Transportation Funding and Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
22 (C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
23 Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
24 mittee on Conduct.
25 (d) Committee chairpersons shall schedule work sessions for measures in the second chamber
26 no later than February 20, 2026. This paragraph does not apply to:
27 (A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
28 (B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, the Joint Com-
29 mittee on Transportation Funding and the Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
30 (C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
